My mom...

1060
01:02:55,140 --> 01:02:57,350
I think she'd be a bit taken aback at first.

1061
01:02:57,680 --> 01:03:00,250
- Why? - At first...

1062
01:03:01,450 --> 01:03:03,720
- My mom is... - In what way?

1063
01:03:03,820 --> 01:03:06,690
You can just speak Korean with my mom. Right.

1064
01:03:07,820 --> 01:03:11,559
To my mother, please speak Korean.

1065
01:03:11,560 --> 01:03:14,959
Or you could teach me perfect English first. Right?

1066
01:03:14,960 --> 01:03:20,130
Right. First, with your speaking. And then, your choice of words.

1067
01:03:20,200 --> 01:03:21,600
I must teach you first.

1068
01:03:21,870 --> 01:03:23,940
Otherwise, she might get the wrong idea.

1069
01:03:25,810 --> 01:03:26,810
Just don't make me speak English.

1070
01:03:26,811 --> 01:03:29,510
Please, just listen to her Korean for a bit.

1071
01:03:30,750 --> 01:03:34,280
- "Don't make her speak English." - But that's really cute.

1072
01:03:38,120 --> 01:03:42,789
And this is an album. I brought this too, just in case...

1073
01:03:42,790 --> 01:03:45,159
Not for sale. Only for friends and family.

1074
01:03:45,160 --> 01:03:46,389
I was curious about this too.

1075
01:03:46,390 --> 01:03:49,260
If you release another album,

1076
01:03:49,330 --> 01:03:51,500
I'll be in the music video.

1077
01:03:52,600 --> 01:03:53,600
Hey, I'd love that.

1078
01:03:53,730 --> 01:03:56,970
I'm trying to make an effort here in my own way.

1079
01:04:02,940 --> 01:04:04,580
- Should we do cheers? - Okay.

1080
01:04:05,450 --> 01:04:09,950
Cheers. This is a little awkward.

1081
01:04:16,260 --> 01:04:17,430
Hey, this is good.

1082
01:04:19,830 --> 01:04:22,399
- I'm so tired. - Let's go get some rest.

1083
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:24,629
- I know, right? Thank you. - Let's go. Let's take a rest.

1084
01:04:24,630 --> 01:04:25,970
I'll really treasure this.

1085
01:04:27,740 --> 01:04:32,010
This looks good. Hey, this place is amazing.

1086
01:04:33,540 --> 01:04:35,910
Today was so draining, wasn't it?

1087
01:04:36,310 --> 01:04:37,810
It was a long day.

1088
01:04:38,810 --> 01:04:40,879
- Hey. - Don't say "hey."

1089
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:43,950
You should correct that too. I like being corrected.

1090
01:04:44,220 --> 01:04:47,319
- It's like calling a friend. - Yes, it does.

1091
01:04:47,320 --> 01:04:50,590
If you want me to be your friend, then you can do that.

1092
01:04:51,130 --> 01:04:53,060
No, I don't want to be just friends.

1093
01:04:53,360 --> 01:04:56,660
Do it one more time, and I'll assume you want to be friends.

1094
01:04:56,730 --> 01:04:58,699
That's what you'd assume?

1095
01:04:58,700 --> 01:05:00,869
I will. Talk nicely, okay?

1096
01:05:00,870 --> 01:05:02,769
- Okay. - That is...

1097
01:05:02,770 --> 01:05:05,909
And I think that's really important.

1098
01:05:05,910 --> 01:05:06,970
Right.

1099
01:05:07,140 --> 01:05:11,380
The way I talk can be sharp and pointed...

1100
01:05:11,650 --> 01:05:14,680
I think I can learn a lot from you.

1101
01:05:15,580 --> 01:05:17,490
I didn't like these.

1102
01:05:17,790 --> 01:05:19,990
"Hey, you're pretty."

1103
01:05:20,820 --> 01:05:22,320
"Hey, you look good today."

1104
01:05:22,460 --> 01:05:27,160
I don't think calling someone "hey" is very affectionate.

1105
01:05:27,800 --> 01:05:30,500
I feel like it's disrespectful to the other person.

1106
01:05:37,640 --> 01:05:41,380
Will I ever feel romantic interest in you again?

1107
01:05:41,540 --> 01:05:44,110
As for now, I don't hold on to a departing ship.

1108
01:05:44,410 --> 01:05:46,680
You're saying that on purpose, aren't you?

1109
01:05:46,750 --> 01:05:48,920
Do you really want me to hate you?

1110
01:05:49,020 --> 01:05:50,650
Then what am I supposed to do?

1111
01:05:50,720 --> 01:05:53,620
The way you keep saying "hey" is a bit of a turn-off.

1112
01:05:54,160 --> 01:05:56,220
I think I'm being gaslighted.

1113
01:05:56,460 --> 01:05:58,390
You were so quick to say that, but now you have nothing to say?

1114
01:05:58,760 --> 01:06:01,700
And she was like, "I told you not to say that."

1115
01:06:01,860 --> 01:06:04,800
Once it's over between us, it's over for good.

1116
01:06:05,100 --> 01:06:07,200
I was feeling really miserable.

1117
01:06:07,900 --> 01:06:10,100
I thought I should make up my mind.

1118
01:06:10,300 --> 01:06:12,310
I thought, "What should I do now?"

1119
01:06:20,380 --> 01:06:21,380
What's that?

1120
01:06:21,880 --> 01:06:23,450
You don't know? It's a new game I'm playing.

1121
01:06:23,750 --> 01:06:24,750
Play Together.

1122
01:06:24,850 --> 01:06:25,850
Okay.

1123
01:06:25,851 --> 01:06:27,220
You can customize your character.

1124
01:06:27,620 --> 01:06:29,659
- Which one should I pick? - That's cute. The pink one.

1125
01:06:29,660 --> 01:06:31,460
- The pink one? Okay. Cool. - Yes.

1126
01:06:33,130 --> 01:06:34,230
Let's see.

1127
01:06:35,030 --> 01:06:36,800
It has a lot of options.

1128
01:06:37,470 --> 01:06:38,970
- Wait. - Goodness.
